description:
&lt;p&gt;The Ward Clerk will give efficient clerical assistance to the Tan y Castell Unit. The provision of an efficient clerical service is essential to ensure the prompt admission, discharge, and transfer of patients.By the nature of the duties, the Ward Clerk will be required to maintain strict confidentiality and will be expected to deal with patients and relatives with courtesy and discretion at all times. The Ward Clerk is responsible to the Ward Managers in providing an efficient clerical service across the wards&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is essential for this post. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date: 15/11/2020 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Adrianne Jones&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Business Support Manager, Regional Services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: adrianne.jones@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 03000 852708 &lt;/p&gt;
